16/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- US President George W Bush reportedly sought Turkish support for Washington's latest road map for the Middle East during a telephone conversation Thursday (15 May). Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan called Bush to express condolences over the terrorist attacks on Westerners in Riyadh. Turkish media reported that Bush praised Turkey's policy with regard to northern Iraq and expressed his administration's readiness to co-operate with Turkey in other fields, including resolution of the Cyprus dispute. (Hurriyet, Milliyet - 16/05/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV - 15/05/03)
